  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Training  C.I.C. and bowel management Spina Bifida</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Children with Spina Bifida have no sensitivity from the bottom down. Sensation and voluntary emptying of the intestine and bladder are not always possible causing urine to &quot;back up&quot; into the kidneys which can cause permanent damage over time to the kidneys or incontinence. Children may have frequent urinary tract infections and pressure sores. The goal of the project is to train nurses/physiotherapists, mothers and children with SB on Clean Intermittent Catheterization CIC and bowel management.</narrative>
  </description>
